      "date": "2011-04-04 18:19:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think kernel supplies the reg file bits?\nWhat's your reproducer?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3d893efdd56ced9e95fdfda74293ed13b99191e0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 8,
        "name": "zhen liang",
        "email": "liang.zhen@live.com",
        "username": "liang"
      },
      "date": "2011-04-05 07:41:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOleg, kernel will supply reg file bits only in vfs_create, my reproducer is a extremely simple program like this:\n\nint\nmain(int argc, char **argv)\n{\n        int fd = open(argv[1], O_CREAT|O_RDWR);\n\n        close(fd);\n        return 0;\n}\n\nand I can crash system very easily by running this like for a few times (rhel5, x86-64), especially on new formated lustre.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
